snippet.textDisplay:
My depression and anxiety keep on bothering me for years.

Suicide had always been on my mind and like all the time, I couldn't care less about anyone anymore. It's like my mind has always been so insensitive and it tells me nothing but how worthless everything I do is. It's fuming mad and bursting of emotions but I don't know how to release all of them.
So if the time comes and I couldn't put up with all of the pressure, anxiety, melancholy and all anymore, before I go, please know that I love you all and I am sorry. I didn't wanna do it, but I can't help myself.
I never wanna kill myself, but sometimes, even just the thought of it gives me a sense of euphoria. And if, for the very last time, I tried it again and works, don't blame yourself. Blame none but me. And I give you the right to be mad, it's the least I could do.

If this triggers you, the reader, I am deeply sorry. I'm just so fucked up right now. I wish you all the best.

snippet.textDisplay: Although this is a song about suicide, it makes me very emotional and reminds me of my wife. She walked out on me forever. We started the marriage on the wrong foot. Always worried about the nitty gritty and did not focus on the bigger picture. We tried to work on things but every time we tried, things broke down. I still love her a lot and wish it had worked out. Now when I don't have her besides me, I feel that I should just have been the bigger person and kept quite when we were arguing on stupid things. Maybe she would have realized eventually. I was still trying to figure it out. It sucks when people don't realize what they mean to others :(

snippet.textDisplay:
Thank you for this song. Thanks you for this beautiful music video that so perfectly captures how someone who is the joy in so many other peoples lives can be suffering. I lost one of my favorite people to suicide in October, and a month later this song came out. The first time I listened, it brought me to my knees. This song perfectly describes every single feeling I felt after losing my friend. It helped me through my grief, and as I continue to grieve the loss of my close friend, I will return to your song over and over to feel understood.
Thank you Lewis Capaldi.

You’re not hurting only yourself, but the people around you. They’ll question everyday if there was something they could’ve done.

STAY STRONG. Please. You’re worth more than everything in the world combined.
My Instagram is @smileyshelbey if you’re ever feeling low. I’m here to talk 🧡🧡
